scenes.label: *from_AC_02_08
texts: Hahah... I guess I'm hungry. How about you?
Sorry. We won't use the lockers again.
I took some deep breaths to cool my head.
We were gonna go that Kabukicho district that the workers mentioned.
I searched it online and found a way to get there fast.
It was in the opposite direction from the station, so we wouldn't run into the Cyber Force Dolls there.
The entrance to the passageway was in the middle of a subway tunnel, with a ladder leading up into a shaft.
This seemed like a passageway meant for regular inspections.
And if we went through it, we would end up in Kabukicho.
It's a bit unsteady, so I'll support you. You climb first.
Momo reached for the ladder enthusiastically, but as she went to put her foot on a rung...
Are you hurt somewhere? Does it hurt to climb? We can treat it, so—
Are you tired? We can take a break here.
What, are you just being stubborn then? Can't help you with that.
After an extraordinary amount of hesitation...
Momo managed to get her reason out.
"Like what?" ...was absolutely not a question I could ask out loud!

scenes.label: *kaisou
texts: So she wasn't wearing any panties.
She was wearing this thing that looked like both an animal costume and pajamas at the same time...but she wasn't wearing any panties.
So, back when we were running around Nakano...
Back when she'd clung to me on my graper...
Back when we'd jumped down to the underpass...
Back when we'd warmed ourselves by the fire...
I'll go first! You just follow me!
Kabukicho was one of the places that suffered a direct hit during Sad Morning. It had been completely destroyed.
After that though, people who'd lost their homes, among others, took to squatting in the ruins. It had turned into a lawless wasteland.
I'd heard that the locals were one of the reasons why the Shinjuku Crater restoration wasn't going as fast as planned.
People of all ages lived there, and there were a bunch of people you could tell weren't all there just from the look in their eyes.
This wasn't a nice place by any measure, but that was exactly why I figured it'd be good for losing our pursuers.
Let's go to Shin-Okubo and grab a taxi.
It was real refreshing to finally get some fresh air after being underground for so long. Feeling good, so I stretched my body a bit.
Finally, I'll be able to go home—
We've been looking for you. We're the police.
The three Cyber Force Dolls parted the crowd and came over to us.
They almost looked at home, wearing those weird outfits in a chaotic place like this.
How did you know we'd come here?
You need to put out your fires properly. With water. You wouldn't want them to spread, now would you?
We used heat sensors to find that fire of yours, then followed your body heat.
We'd like you to come with us, please.
...Damn. Heat tracing. Looks like I really underestimated you.

scenes.label: *load
texts: All right, so I'm gonna have to take you guys more seriously next time.
This place wasn't normal. The locals might get involved if we started messing with the police, and that wouldn't end well for us.
Kabukicho was just that messed up.
Sneaking out without drawing any attention would've been ideal, but we'd been found, so hanging around wasn't a good idea.

scenes.label: *select1
texts: You thought the same thing, huh?
